POLICE say they are dealing with a “serious ongoing incident” which has seen block of flats closed off throughout the night.
Detectives and police officers are currently carrying out checks at an area around the property at the junction of Cumbernauld Road and Provan Road in the Riddrie area of Glasgow.
It’s also caused early morning traffic chaos with the road next to it blocked off.
One woman who lives in a nearby flat said an incident had taken place in the street around 10.30pm last night.
She added: “We were then woken up by detectives doing door to door checks around 1am in the morning.
“There were forensics officers going about in white suits as well.
“No-one will really tell us what it happening.”
Police said the were so far unable to provide any more details.
